sentences: Rasmus Seebach (Danish: [ˈʁɑsmus ˈse̝ːpɑk]; born 28 March 1980) is a Danish singer-songwriter and record producer who had his solo-debut with the Danish language single "Engel" (English: "Angel") in April 2009.

Rasmus Seebach (Danish: [ˈʁɑsmus ˈse̝ːpɑk]; born 28 March 1980) is a Danish singer-songwriter and record producer who had his solo-debut with the Danish language single "Engel" (English: "Angel") in April 2009.
His self-titled debut album consists of 12 tracks and was released on 28 September 2009, containing among others the singles "Engel" and "Glad igen" (English: "Happy again").
In 2012 he recorded a duet version of "Say You, Say Me" with Lionel Richie which was featured on Richie's album Tuskegee.
Seebach has written and produced songs for Danish and international artists since the late 1990s.
The two wrote the music for the charity song "Hvor små vi er" (English: "How small we are") for the victims of the 2004 Indian Ocean earthquake and tsunami.
Rasmus Seebach is a son of Tommy Seebach, about whom he has also written a song, namely "Den jeg er" (English: "Who I am").
